 {"id":"bd-p8i4s","title":"task(perf-foundation): automate hotspot extraction across CPU, allocation, and syscall pressure","description":"Background:\nOptimization choices should be driven by a ranked understanding of where time and resources are actually being spent. In FrankenTUI that likely spans CPU-heavy render code, allocation-heavy text/layout work, syscall-heavy presentation paths, and subprocess-heavy doctor workflows.\n\nGoal:\nCreate the profiling and hotspot extraction lane that converts raw profiler output into a stable, comparable set of candidate bottlenecks.","design":"Work packages:\n- Define profiling modes appropriate to the workspace: CPU, allocation, syscall, and workflow-level timing.\n- Normalize profiler outputs into a common hotspot table with stage, location, percent contribution, and category labels.\n- Require artifact linkage from hotspot records back to fixture IDs and baseline IDs.\n- Document when hotspots are likely measurement artifacts versus genuine EV opportunities.\n- Produce a ranking format that later scoring logic can consume directly.","acceptance_criteria":"1. Later optimization beads can point to a stable hotspot record instead of free-form profiling output.\n2. Hotspot extraction covers all major resource classes relevant to FrankenTUI, not CPU alone.\n3. The bead makes it obvious how to distinguish dominant bottlenecks from noisy or non-reproducible findings.","notes":"This bead operationalizes the 'profile first' rule so it becomes a workflow rather than an aspiration.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-14T18:46:25.437629336Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-18T00:27:22.612620194Z","closed_at":"2026-03-18T00:27:22.612081805Z","close_reason":"Hotspot extraction infrastructure in hotspot_extraction.rs: 4 ProfilingModes (Cpu, Allocation, Syscall, Workflow), Hotspot builder with symbol/mode/contribution/location/confidence/artifact-flag, HotspotTable with ranked/actionable